WEBVTT

00:00.453 --> 00:02.490
<i>Previously on Blood & Treasure...</i>

00:02.496 --> 00:04.457
REECE: <i>The theft of Antony
wasn't even discovered</i>

00:04.463 --> 00:06.646
till the morning shift.
News hasn't been alerted yet.

00:06.652 --> 00:07.997
SHAW: <i>I missed out on my slice</i>

00:08.003 --> 00:09.674
of the finder's fee for Antony,

00:09.680 --> 00:11.860
and I'll be damned if I
get cut out of Cleo, too.

00:11.876 --> 00:13.339
All right, you can come along.

00:13.345 --> 00:15.347
- And I...
- You won't regret it.

00:15.353 --> 00:16.475
DANNY: It's her.

00:16.481 --> 00:17.977
[GUNS COCK]

00:17.983 --> 00:20.041
DANNY: You're making a huge mistake.

00:20.047 --> 00:21.980
Cleopatra's gone.

00:21.986 --> 00:24.744
Whoever attacked me after
looking into Zara Farouk

00:24.750 --> 00:26.317
<i>is getting desperate.</i>

00:26.323 --> 00:27.818
DANNY: <i>Do you know
anything about who it is?</i>

00:27.824 --> 00:29.841
GWEN: <i>No, but I know
this belongs to him.</i>

00:29.847 --> 00:31.960
DANNY: Reece gives these
to family and friends.

00:32.029 --> 00:33.858
- That's him.
- LEXI: Yates?

00:33.864 --> 00:36.060
Yates is more the kind to take orders

00:36.066 --> 00:38.025
than give them. Maybe...

00:38.031 --> 00:40.138
the real bad guy has been in front of us

00:40.144 --> 00:42.103
<i>all this time.</i>

00:42.957 --> 00:45.891
- _
- [BELL CLANGING]

00:46.006 --> 00:47.668
That's crazy.

00:47.674 --> 00:48.773
LEXI: Are you kidding?

00:48.779 --> 00:50.439
Everything finally makes sense.

00:50.445 --> 00:52.378
Have no idea what you're talking about,

00:52.384 --> 00:54.784
yet somehow I feel like I
haven't missed anything.

00:54.790 --> 00:56.824
We found Cleopatra.

00:56.825 --> 00:58.125
No way.

00:58.194 --> 01:00.486
Yes, and she was taken,
along with Antony.

01:00.492 --> 01:03.059
- By who?
- That's what we're arguing about.

01:03.065 --> 01:04.584
Ah, Father Chuck, hi,

01:04.590 --> 01:05.995
- so, nice to meet you.
- Hi.

01:06.001 --> 01:07.863
I've heard so much about you.
I'm Dr. Ana Castillo.

01:07.869 --> 01:09.935
- I'm gonna make some coffee, okay?
- Uh, o-okay,

01:09.941 --> 01:13.076
yeah, sure, uh, make yourself at home.

01:13.567 --> 01:16.067
- Father.
- Agent Karlsson.

01:17.510 --> 01:19.291
At the moment, I am acting

01:19.297 --> 01:21.278
outside of proper channels.

01:21.284 --> 01:22.715
Okay.

01:22.721 --> 01:24.214
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

01:24.782 --> 01:27.283
- Hey, watch it.
- Who are you?

01:27.537 --> 01:29.804
I'm Shaw. You got anything to eat?

01:29.810 --> 01:31.603
CASTILLO: Well, I'm making
coffee over here, and

01:31.609 --> 01:33.248
it looks like he's got
a lovely antipasto...

01:33.254 --> 01:35.209
We having, like, a, uh, treasure
hunt meeting or something?

01:35.215 --> 01:36.915
- Man, I am starving.
- DANNY: You know what?

01:36.921 --> 01:38.683
- Me, too.
- He's got some candy hidden away

01:38.689 --> 01:39.960
in the bottom drawer on the left.

01:39.966 --> 01:41.432
FATHER CHUCK: Okay, everybody stop

01:41.438 --> 01:43.315
what you're doing right now.

01:44.185 --> 01:45.551
[GRUNTING]

01:45.557 --> 01:46.658
Okay.

01:46.727 --> 01:48.026
First of all,

01:48.549 --> 01:50.929
- is anyone else showing up at my home?
- Nope.

01:50.935 --> 01:52.222
I think we're all here.

01:52.228 --> 01:53.928
I swear. I just came home for lunch.

01:53.934 --> 01:55.310
I'm glad you're here, Chuck.

01:55.316 --> 01:56.656
We could use someone objective

01:56.662 --> 01:58.262
- to help us decide.
- Yeah.

01:58.433 --> 01:59.584
Decide what?

02:00.634 --> 02:02.233
We've known all along

02:02.512 --> 02:04.947
that Farouk was planning
to use Antony and Cleopatra

02:04.953 --> 02:07.220
somehow in an attack.

02:07.226 --> 02:10.215
His crew is still out there,
and they have a bioweapon.

02:10.558 --> 02:12.023
Some people

02:12.029 --> 02:13.647
believe I have a blind spot

02:13.653 --> 02:15.586
that is preventing me
from seeing the truth.

02:15.592 --> 02:17.655
But I think we're wasting
time we could be using

02:17.661 --> 02:19.153
looking for the real bad guys.

02:19.159 --> 02:21.331
So we'll make our case.

02:21.659 --> 02:22.928
You tell us who's crazy.

02:22.996 --> 02:24.362
Only one of you is crazy?

02:24.431 --> 02:25.863
[LAUGHS]

02:25.933 --> 02:27.399
- Sorry.
- Right, then.

02:27.405 --> 02:29.472
May I? I found the evidence

02:29.478 --> 02:31.568
and I'm the actual police officer here.

02:31.840 --> 02:35.008
Plus, your, um... pants
are covered in candy.

02:36.473 --> 02:38.539
Ready to tag in as cocounsel if needed.

02:39.197 --> 02:40.826
So, Fabi was running a parallel

02:40.832 --> 02:42.617
investigation into Karim Farouk.

02:42.623 --> 02:44.991
After he died, I obtained some evidence

02:44.997 --> 02:47.531
and I found a check written
out to a Zara Farouk.

02:47.537 --> 02:48.937
Huh, interesting.

02:48.943 --> 02:51.070
I thought Karim Farouk
was a made-up name.

02:51.076 --> 02:53.390
DANNY: The man we know as
Karim Farouk's real name

02:53.459 --> 02:55.059
is Rasheed Hegazi.

02:55.127 --> 02:57.127
But he may have chosen the nom de guerre

02:57.133 --> 02:58.432
of Karim Farouk for a reason.

02:58.438 --> 03:00.160
GWEN: I haven't been
able to find out much

03:00.166 --> 03:02.833
about Zara Farouk, but
I know she was Egyptian

03:02.839 --> 03:05.298
and she died of a rare mycotoxin.

03:05.304 --> 03:06.566
So she was a tomb raider.

03:06.572 --> 03:09.606
- How do you know?
- Mycotoxin is a mutation

03:09.612 --> 03:12.112
of the toxic mold created
by the breaking down

03:12.118 --> 03:13.443
of mummified tissue.

03:13.512 --> 03:14.838
Mummy cancer?

03:14.844 --> 03:16.489
You said that couldn't hurt me.

03:16.495 --> 03:19.115
No, generally it doesn't in
modern times. When did she die?

03:19.121 --> 03:20.231
1990s.

03:20.237 --> 03:21.985
That sounds pretty damn modern to me.

03:22.053 --> 03:24.020
GWEN: The same toxin was found

03:24.026 --> 03:25.358
in a lab in Russia...

03:25.364 --> 03:28.137
alongside a body...
that it'd been tested on.

03:28.143 --> 03:30.159
DANNY: Farouk's men have weaponized it.

03:30.165 --> 03:31.864
That's not a coincidence.

03:31.870 --> 03:33.593
Who wrote the check to Zara Farouk?

03:33.599 --> 03:34.852
GWEN: Well, I've been trying

03:34.858 --> 03:36.224
to find that out.

03:36.230 --> 03:37.997
But the bank stonewalled me.

03:38.003 --> 03:40.299
I couldn't obtain a warrant
because the evidence was...

03:40.611 --> 03:43.160
[INHALES SHARPLY]
You know, obtained illegally.

03:43.229 --> 03:44.854
But the call seemed to have

03:44.860 --> 03:46.539
sent up some sort of flare

03:46.545 --> 03:49.212
because, uh, later I was
attacked in my apartment.

03:49.218 --> 03:50.385
Oh, my God. Are you okay?

03:50.391 --> 03:52.115
She's fine, but more importantly,

03:52.121 --> 03:53.539
all the evidence was taken.

03:53.545 --> 03:55.964
- And Gwen, badass that she is...
- Thank you.

03:55.970 --> 03:57.386
You got it, sister.

03:57.392 --> 03:58.950
... tracked the person who attacked her

03:58.956 --> 04:02.290
to Rick Yates, head of
security for Jacob Reece,

04:02.484 --> 04:04.062
proving that he's the most

04:04.068 --> 04:06.124
likely mastermind behind Farouk.

04:06.130 --> 04:08.397
- Objection. Fine.
- SHAW: Dude. We're not in court.

04:08.403 --> 04:10.465
- Then I call BS.
- On which part?

04:10.535 --> 04:11.800
All of it.

04:11.869 --> 04:13.898
This whole theory makes no sense.

04:13.904 --> 04:16.406
What does Reece have to gain
by supporting a terrorist?

04:16.411 --> 04:19.173
LEXI: Uh, his family made
most its money in oil.

04:19.180 --> 04:21.659
More instability, the price goes up.

04:21.867 --> 04:24.901
And as a bonus, Farouk
loots blood antiquities,

04:24.907 --> 04:26.682
which then makes its way to Reece,

04:26.688 --> 04:27.979
who launders it through his

04:27.985 --> 04:29.651
museum to make it all legitimate.

04:29.657 --> 04:31.353
Makes a lot of sense.

04:31.359 --> 04:33.485
- DANNY: It's ridiculous.
- You're ridiculous.

04:33.491 --> 04:35.800
You know when instability
doesn't help your company?

04:35.806 --> 04:38.093
When your own pipeline gets blown up.

04:38.104 --> 04:39.769
The company took a
half-billion dollar hit

04:39.775 --> 04:40.942
when Farouk attacked it.

04:40.948 --> 04:42.481
It's not a great path to profit.

04:42.487 --> 04:45.269
Maybe Reece lost control
of his attack dog.

04:45.275 --> 04:47.579
And maybe you're the
one with the blind spot.

04:47.893 --> 04:50.176
Farouk's dead, Lexi, and
now you want to redirect

04:50.182 --> 04:52.341
your rage towards someone new because

04:52.347 --> 04:54.645
you still blame yourself
for your father's death.

05:01.340 --> 05:04.234
So, I'm guessing we don't
get to rule on this.

05:04.240 --> 05:06.204
[DANNY SIGHS] I'll be,
I'll be right back.

05:10.877 --> 05:12.810
I'm sorry.

05:12.989 --> 05:14.989
I shouldn't have said that.

05:18.076 --> 05:20.176
Don't you think that
if you didn't suspect

05:20.182 --> 05:21.561
something was wrong with Reece,

05:21.567 --> 05:23.351
you wouldn't be so defensive?

05:24.550 --> 05:26.182
If I am right,

05:26.251 --> 05:27.651
and Reece was behind Farouk,

05:27.657 --> 05:29.081
maybe he's the reason Farouk

05:29.087 --> 05:30.917
was so hard to catch all that time.

05:30.923 --> 05:33.423
What if Farouk only needed
Antony and Cleopatra

05:33.429 --> 05:35.296
because Reece wanted them and that theft

05:35.302 --> 05:37.229
was just his way of
keeping them for himself?

05:37.235 --> 05:39.807
Are you kidding? He wants
credit for finding them.

05:40.795 --> 05:42.762
This is about legacy for him.

05:42.768 --> 05:45.401
About being a part of history.

05:45.470 --> 05:48.277
I do know a group that
wants Antony and Cleopatra

05:48.283 --> 05:50.636
and doesn't want anyone
to know where they are.

05:50.642 --> 05:52.075
Who, the Brotherhood of Serapis?

05:52.081 --> 05:53.781
- And how do they work?
- Oh, here we go.

05:53.912 --> 05:56.046
They place agents, people like Fabi,

05:56.114 --> 05:58.114
into organizations to manipulate them

05:58.120 --> 05:59.663
from behind the scenes.

06:00.314 --> 06:01.680
Now, I don't doubt that Yates

06:01.686 --> 06:03.386
was behind the attack on Gwen.

06:03.455 --> 06:05.670
I just think he works
for the Brotherhood.

06:05.676 --> 06:07.453
- Oh, come on.
- What?

06:07.459 --> 06:08.869
Why is that crazier than Reece

06:08.875 --> 06:10.332
being a terrorist mastermind?

06:10.338 --> 06:11.856
- [EXHALES]
- You don't think the Brotherhood's

06:11.862 --> 06:13.792
gonna keep tabs on everybody

06:13.798 --> 06:16.132
who has the interest and
means of finding Cleopatra?

06:16.201 --> 06:18.761
Now they can frame Reece
for the disappearance.

06:19.019 --> 06:21.166
To stay a secret society
for thousands of years,

06:21.172 --> 06:22.482
you get real good at finding

06:22.488 --> 06:24.078
people to take the fall for you.

06:24.142 --> 06:26.075
I know who the bad guy is.

06:26.144 --> 06:27.910
It's Reece.

06:27.979 --> 06:30.480
Everything runs through Reece.

06:30.548 --> 06:32.415
You're just too blind to see it.

06:32.484 --> 06:35.084
Lexi, you're wrong.
I know it in my heart.

06:35.153 --> 06:38.002
And while we're fighting each
other, we're losing time.

06:42.826 --> 06:45.594
What kind of relationship do
we have if you can't trust me?

06:46.182 --> 06:48.296
I could ask you the same thing.

06:50.609 --> 06:52.042
Look...

06:52.071 --> 06:54.871
You do things your way
and I'll do it mine.

06:55.705 --> 06:57.543
Good luck with your way.

07:05.477 --> 07:10.594
<font color="#dcc12c">- Synced and corrected by medvidecek007 -
- www.addic7ed.com -</font>

07:18.381 --> 07:20.782
- _
- [PHONE BUZZING]

07:28.171 --> 07:29.637
- Hello.
- DANNY: Simon.

07:29.705 --> 07:31.372
This is Danny McNamara.

07:31.440 --> 07:32.806
<i>Uh,</i>

07:32.812 --> 07:35.543
- it's usually Lexi who calls me.
<i>- Yeah.</i>

07:35.549 --> 07:37.983
Yeah, I wanted you
all to myself this time.

07:38.113 --> 07:39.613
Right.

07:39.682 --> 07:41.382
<i>Hey, have you found anything yet?</i>

07:41.388 --> 07:43.243
From the bug you have inside Serapis?

07:43.249 --> 07:44.514
<i>Any indication of where</i>

07:44.520 --> 07:46.119
<i>they've taken Antony and Cleopatra?</i>

07:46.189 --> 07:48.489
No. No, I'm afraid not.

07:48.558 --> 07:51.725
I've been plowing through the audio.

07:51.794 --> 07:53.694
Uh, it's just mostly

07:53.762 --> 07:56.497
hours and hours of silence.

07:56.566 --> 07:58.499
Which, I suppose, isn't surprising,

07:58.568 --> 08:00.367
uh, given that the bug's in a crypt.

08:00.436 --> 08:03.337
Okay, well, please let me know
the moment you hear anything.

08:03.406 --> 08:04.704
<i>Yeah, uh, Danny.</i>

08:04.772 --> 08:06.539
I'm still in Rome.

08:06.545 --> 08:08.937
I-I don't know if you, uh, needed a hand

08:08.943 --> 08:10.376
in your adventures or...

08:10.445 --> 08:12.912
I think we'll be fine. Thanks.

08:12.980 --> 08:14.414
Hello?

08:14.482 --> 08:15.848
He...

08:18.015 --> 08:20.449
- Where are you going?
- Egypt.

08:20.455 --> 08:23.089
- To see Sharif Ghazal.
- From the Cultural Ministry?

08:23.095 --> 08:25.887
Oh, that. That's his cover job.
He's actually in intelligence.

08:25.893 --> 08:27.953
And we thought he was
working for Farouk.

08:27.959 --> 08:29.442
That file Fabi was working on is

08:29.448 --> 08:30.926
one I took from Ghazal's safe.

08:30.932 --> 08:33.292
So you're gonna go to Ghazal,
you're gonna talk to him

08:33.298 --> 08:35.331
and find out who he really works for?

08:35.337 --> 08:36.563
Talk, hang him out a window

08:36.568 --> 08:38.062
by a lamp cord, whatever works.

08:38.068 --> 08:39.482
I will come with you.

08:39.488 --> 08:40.635
Thanks but no thanks.

08:40.642 --> 08:42.508
Lexi, we are on the...

08:42.514 --> 08:43.937
[CLEARS THROAT] Same side.

08:44.867 --> 08:46.846
I also think that Reece is responsible

08:46.852 --> 08:48.409
and I can help you prove it.

08:48.415 --> 08:49.617
Huh.

08:50.939 --> 08:52.339
Team Lexi and Gwen?

08:52.831 --> 08:54.515
If that is the order you prefer.

08:54.521 --> 08:57.226
All right. I can work with that.

09:01.362 --> 09:04.797
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

09:04.866 --> 09:06.799
[TOILET FLUSHING]

09:08.302 --> 09:10.068
Wh-Where did all the ladies go?

09:10.137 --> 09:12.009
- Egypt.
- Aw, man.

09:12.015 --> 09:13.821
I wasn't in there that long.

09:13.827 --> 09:16.107
Yo, man, the ladies just teamed up.

09:16.176 --> 09:17.643
Now we got to do our thing.

09:18.249 --> 09:20.646
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

09:20.714 --> 09:22.247
You think the Brotherhood
is behind this.

09:22.316 --> 09:24.583
Let's find out where they
took Antony and Cleopatra.

09:24.652 --> 09:25.778
You and me.

09:26.720 --> 09:29.120
Simon Hardwick put a bug in Serapis

09:29.189 --> 09:31.590
to keep tabs on their hunt
for Antony and Cleopatra.

09:31.596 --> 09:33.373
He's been going through
the recordings to see

09:33.379 --> 09:35.144
if he can find out
where they were taken.

09:35.150 --> 09:37.313
Okay. That's a good plan. But...

09:37.593 --> 09:39.043
If Yates works for them,

09:39.049 --> 09:40.649
don't you want to know what he's up to?

09:41.674 --> 09:43.769
I got eyes in every country.

09:43.837 --> 09:45.569
I can track him down for you.

09:45.638 --> 09:48.139
Maybe he leads us right
to the proof we need.

09:48.208 --> 09:49.607
That's...

09:49.613 --> 09:52.319
That's actually a good idea.

09:53.025 --> 09:54.618
Okay.

09:56.183 --> 09:57.748
<i>Predator</i> handshake.

10:00.253 --> 10:01.686
Let's do this.

10:02.358 --> 10:04.365
- _
- LEXI: So, the last time I was here,

10:04.371 --> 10:06.187
I did a bump-lift to
take someone's badge

10:06.193 --> 10:07.751
and used it to get into the building.

10:07.757 --> 10:09.690
But Ghazal's office
is a little trickier.

10:09.696 --> 10:11.225
The door's secure, but
there's a glass divider

10:11.231 --> 10:12.685
above his door that's unlocked,

10:12.691 --> 10:15.192
- and I was able to get in...
- How about I use this?

10:15.492 --> 10:17.220
LEXI: Okay, I have to say,

10:17.226 --> 10:18.765
being on this side of law enforcement

10:18.771 --> 10:21.439
definitely has its advantages.

10:23.409 --> 10:25.175
So Ghazal hasn't come back yet?

10:25.244 --> 10:26.644
Not today, ma'am.

10:27.358 --> 10:28.842
Is he, uh, ever late?

10:28.848 --> 10:31.315
Not since I've worked here. Eight years.

10:31.509 --> 10:32.808
Can you give us a moment?

10:32.814 --> 10:35.615
GWEN: Interpol business.
It's classified.

10:35.621 --> 10:37.020
I'll get my superior.

10:43.963 --> 10:45.329
Oh...

10:45.398 --> 10:47.297
Bloody fantastic.

10:47.367 --> 10:49.091
Either Ghazal is on the run

10:49.097 --> 10:50.763
or he's already dead.

10:50.769 --> 10:52.168
How can you be sure?

10:52.174 --> 10:54.107
Someone cleaned out the safe.

10:54.239 --> 10:55.894
Or maybe he knows Reece are cutting

10:55.900 --> 10:57.412
loose threads and disappeared.

10:57.476 --> 11:00.209
Or he didn't, and Reece disappeared him.

11:01.521 --> 11:02.812
Oh.

11:02.881 --> 11:04.714
Someone took the hard drive.

11:04.783 --> 11:06.883
Not looking good for Ghazal.

11:07.302 --> 11:09.069
I'll find out where he lives.

