Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

11:19.365 --> 11:21.677
_

11:21.683 --> 11:24.129
MAJOR REECE: We've
already laid 400 miles

11:24.135 --> 11:26.769
of pipeline without a single fatality.

11:27.697 --> 11:30.706
Look, we both know that
this is a shakedown.

11:30.775 --> 11:33.575
Just tell me what it's gonna cost me.

11:33.644 --> 11:36.011
Jacob, I'm on the phone,
you know better than that.

11:36.017 --> 11:37.440
I'm sorry, sir.

11:38.849 --> 11:40.716
Fine. Do it.

11:40.785 --> 11:42.885
Just don't pay from the
Reece Corporate account.

11:42.953 --> 11:44.219
[HANGS UP PHONE]

11:44.288 --> 11:46.622
What are you doing over
there, Jacob, making a mess?

11:46.690 --> 11:48.199
What is this?

11:54.856 --> 11:56.957
Well, how about that?

11:57.239 --> 12:00.035
That, my boy, is Cleopatra,

12:00.103 --> 12:01.537
the last queen of Egypt.

12:01.605 --> 12:04.205
That's me when I was in the army.

12:04.274 --> 12:06.490
We'd captured this German officer...

12:06.498 --> 12:07.807
Krug was his name.

12:08.011 --> 12:11.746
You see, Cleopatra's been
lost for a very long time,

12:12.213 --> 12:14.313
but Krug told me he knew where she was.

12:14.414 --> 12:17.218
- So you found her?
- Nope.

12:17.287 --> 12:18.886
But this picture,

12:19.711 --> 12:22.223
it lit a fire in me.

12:22.292 --> 12:23.724
Suddenly, finding Cleopatra

12:23.730 --> 12:25.864
was the most important
thing in the world.

12:26.120 --> 12:28.287
So I went looking for her.

12:28.293 --> 12:29.893
If she's out there somewhere,

12:29.899 --> 12:31.983
this lady doesn't want to be found.

12:38.232 --> 12:40.623
_

12:43.313 --> 12:44.512
[GRUNTING]

12:55.492 --> 12:56.791
[GRUNTS]

12:59.479 --> 13:01.454
You shouldn't be down there.

13:01.460 --> 13:03.360
[CHUCKLES] You speak English.

13:03.366 --> 13:05.199
Did you not see the signs back there?

13:05.205 --> 13:07.873
Uh, yeah, yeah, I saw the signs, but...

13:07.879 --> 13:10.580
But you thought they
did not apply to you?

13:11.047 --> 13:14.715
Look, you mind chastising me
after you help me up?

13:23.252 --> 13:25.952
[GRUNTING]

13:29.225 --> 13:31.291
You must be my guardian angel.

13:31.360 --> 13:32.661
[CHUCKLES]

13:34.253 --> 13:36.586
What were you doing down there?

13:36.765 --> 13:39.299
Uh, exploring.

13:39.703 --> 13:42.015
I'm a student backpacking around.

13:42.021 --> 13:43.970
You are Jacob Reece III.

13:44.040 --> 13:45.839
[CHUCKLES]

13:45.908 --> 13:47.341
You know who I am?

13:47.410 --> 13:48.826
The Chalice of the Ptolemies

13:48.832 --> 13:50.549
you're looking for is long gone,

13:50.612 --> 13:53.047
taken by grave robbers like you.

13:54.149 --> 13:56.715
[LAUGHS] Now hold on a minute.

13:56.784 --> 13:58.751
I'm not a grave robber.

13:58.819 --> 14:01.354
Okay? It belongs in a museum
for the whole world to see.

14:01.423 --> 14:03.052
[SCOFFS]

14:03.560 --> 14:04.757
Okay, look.

14:04.763 --> 14:05.820
How about this?

14:05.826 --> 14:07.893
[BOTH SIGH]

14:07.962 --> 14:10.430
I need a guide and interpreter,

14:10.498 --> 14:12.198
clearly.

14:12.960 --> 14:14.344
I'll pay you three times

14:14.350 --> 14:16.131
what you're making right now,

14:16.137 --> 14:18.094
and when I find what I'm looking for,

14:18.100 --> 14:20.573
you'll be right there to
make sure I keep my word.

14:23.078 --> 14:24.674
Save your money.

14:25.346 --> 14:28.114
I know you're trying to find
Antony and Cleopatra.

14:29.109 --> 14:31.234
They are long gone as well.

14:32.932 --> 14:34.664
Well, if you're right,

14:34.921 --> 14:36.268
then you stand to make a lot

14:36.274 --> 14:37.860
of money while we keep looking.

14:44.565 --> 14:46.498
[SIGHS]

14:46.567 --> 14:49.568
I'm Zara. Zara Farouk.

14:49.636 --> 14:51.406
It's very nice to meet you, Zara.

14:51.789 --> 14:54.573
Nice to met you, Jay.

15:00.146 --> 15:02.110
_

15:02.233 --> 15:04.498
FATHER CHUCK: <i>My friends in
the Vatican Foreign Ministry</i>

15:04.504 --> 15:06.551
are figuring out who Zara Farouk was.

15:06.557 --> 15:08.839
Somebody has done a very good job

15:08.855 --> 15:11.822
of removing almost any
trace of her existence.

15:11.891 --> 15:13.323
<i>Almost</i> any trace?

15:13.518 --> 15:15.151
They found the same thing that Gwen did:

15:15.157 --> 15:16.823
her name on a hospital register

15:16.829 --> 15:18.859
from when she checked herself
in with the mummy cancer.

15:18.865 --> 15:21.131
Oh, for God's sakes, is that
what we're calling it now?

15:21.200 --> 15:22.466
It's just easier to remember.

15:22.535 --> 15:24.257
Anyway, when she died,

15:24.263 --> 15:26.141
an imam was requested.

15:26.205 --> 15:28.271
That's the last info we have on her.

15:28.340 --> 15:30.363
Now, I know it's a shot in

15:30.369 --> 15:32.548
the dark, but some mosques

15:32.612 --> 15:34.612
use handwritten records.

15:34.680 --> 15:36.480
That'd be pretty easy for anyone

15:36.548 --> 15:39.115
trying to clean up a
paper trail to miss.

15:39.183 --> 15:40.564
Well, it makes sense that she would

15:40.570 --> 15:42.143
go to a hospital near where she lives.

15:42.149 --> 15:43.526
Gives you an area to search in.

15:43.532 --> 15:46.752
Exactly. Now, I have
an imam friend in Egypt

15:46.758 --> 15:48.334
who is looking into it.

15:48.340 --> 15:50.313
He's gonna figure out
which mosque she went to,

15:50.319 --> 15:53.294
and then he's gonna send
us whatever he finds.

15:53.363 --> 15:54.563
What'd you find out?

15:54.632 --> 15:56.632
Well, I've been reading
up about the body

15:56.700 --> 15:57.966
that was found in the lab.

15:58.035 --> 16:00.205
He was a scientist who
apparently worked for Farouk.

16:00.211 --> 16:02.266
He died from the same
symptoms that Zara did,

16:02.272 --> 16:03.701
only massively accelerated.

16:03.707 --> 16:05.908
So what killed her in months,
killed him in minutes.

16:05.976 --> 16:07.543
Yeesh.

16:07.611 --> 16:09.878
That is grim.

16:09.947 --> 16:11.146
Yeah.

16:11.214 --> 16:14.149
I'm just trying to figure
out why all the effort

16:14.217 --> 16:15.817
into weaponizing something

16:15.886 --> 16:18.566
when there are far greater
toxins already out there?

16:18.572 --> 16:23.087
Yeah. It seems like Farouk
didn't just want to kill people,

16:24.132 --> 16:26.433
he wanted to make sure that
they suffered like she did.

16:26.439 --> 16:28.205
Yeah, well, whoever we're dealing with

16:28.211 --> 16:29.410
is some kind of awful,

16:29.416 --> 16:31.995
so I would tell your friend
in Egypt to be careful.

16:35.869 --> 16:37.971
_

16:41.507 --> 16:44.307
SHAW: So my guy tracked Yates
from the airport to here.

16:44.313 --> 16:46.781
- This is Yates' place?
- Didn't say.

16:46.849 --> 16:48.348
How long ago did he get here?

16:48.354 --> 16:49.554
Didn't say.

16:49.560 --> 16:52.103
Did he come directly to this
house or make any stops?

16:54.057 --> 16:55.129
Didn't say?

16:55.135 --> 16:56.588
I told my man that Yates is a

16:56.594 --> 16:58.597
professional and to keep his distance.

16:58.785 --> 17:00.586
Didn't have much time
to dig into things.

17:00.592 --> 17:02.492
Okay, but you're sure we're not watching

17:02.498 --> 17:04.090
an empty house right now?

17:04.097 --> 17:06.933
Man, Yates went in there
and hasn't come out yet.

17:07.502 --> 17:08.833
Okay.

17:15.833 --> 17:19.189
So, um, you and Lexi
broken up again, or...?

17:19.194 --> 17:20.351
No.

17:20.790 --> 17:22.415
Good, good.

17:23.371 --> 17:25.931
I wasn't trying to move in
on your territory or nothing.

17:25.936 --> 17:28.237
I was just checking in
on the team morale.

17:28.278 --> 17:30.591
Team morale's fine.

17:30.659 --> 17:32.558
We all want the same thing.

17:32.627 --> 17:34.093
Money.

17:34.162 --> 17:36.162
To stop a terrorist attack.

17:36.231 --> 17:38.998
Oh, yeah, of course, but, you know...

17:39.339 --> 17:41.440
I mean, heroes got to eat, right?

17:41.446 --> 17:42.645
[CHUCKLES]

17:44.005 --> 17:45.904
Where are they going?

17:45.973 --> 17:48.441
You said they went to question Ghazal.

17:48.510 --> 17:50.743
Guess now we know whose house this is.

17:50.811 --> 17:52.445
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

17:52.514 --> 17:53.699
Come on.

18:04.274 --> 18:05.406
[WHISTLES]

18:06.730 --> 18:08.152
What are you doing here?

18:08.158 --> 18:09.524
We're following Yates.

18:09.530 --> 18:10.763
LEXI: Yates?

18:10.956 --> 18:12.823
Well, if Yates came to Ghazal's house,

18:12.829 --> 18:14.428
then Ghazal is definitely dead.

18:14.434 --> 18:15.860
Oh, for sure, yeah.

18:16.232 --> 18:17.731
Office was cleared out.

18:17.737 --> 18:19.437
- [ENGINE STARTS]
- Yates is cleaning up.

18:22.432 --> 18:23.831
It's Yates.

18:25.079 --> 18:26.930
Yates!

18:27.514 --> 18:30.215
LEXI: Danny! Danny!

18:31.118 --> 18:33.018
Danny!

18:35.589 --> 18:36.770
Yates!

18:38.525 --> 18:39.624
[GRUNTING]

18:44.923 --> 18:46.122
Buckle up.

18:46.128 --> 18:47.761
[TIRES SCREECHING]

18:47.767 --> 18:49.334
[SHAW WHOOPS]

19:03.382 --> 19:05.482
[WHOOPS]

19:06.385 --> 19:07.630
[WOMAN SHOUTS]

19:07.636 --> 19:09.536
[CAR HORN HONKS]

19:15.786 --> 19:18.520
Hold up, hold up, you
going the wrong way.

19:18.526 --> 19:21.394
Oh, shut up, Shaw! She's concentrating.

19:21.400 --> 19:23.866
You do know where we're going, right?

19:46.759 --> 19:48.526
[SPUTTERS]

19:48.532 --> 19:49.750
Hi.

19:50.497 --> 19:51.596
[GROANING]

19:51.664 --> 19:53.631
[CAR HORN HONKS]

19:53.700 --> 19:55.633
[TIRES SCREECH]

19:55.835 --> 19:56.900
No!

19:58.338 --> 20:01.306
Yates! No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no.

20:04.077 --> 20:06.311
Who are you working for?

20:09.883 --> 20:11.751
- LEXI: Danny.
- Aah!

20:27.898 --> 20:29.930
_

20:31.641 --> 20:33.807
Why do you have to go back?

20:36.818 --> 20:39.385
[SIGHS] It's been noticed
that I haven't actually been

20:39.391 --> 20:40.991
spending a lot of time at the company.

20:41.615 --> 20:44.383
I knew you would leave one day.

20:44.452 --> 20:46.385
[SCOFFS]

20:46.454 --> 20:48.305
This was always just play for you.

20:48.311 --> 20:49.516
Zara, I...

20:54.228 --> 20:56.862
You can come to New York with me.

20:58.397 --> 21:01.134
You think your father would like that?

21:02.027 --> 21:05.104
Wait, does he even know about us?

21:07.441 --> 21:08.811
No.

21:10.773 --> 21:12.740
But he can't tell me what to do.

21:12.746 --> 21:15.548
You said he threatened to cut
you off if you didn't return.

21:15.554 --> 21:17.788
O-Okay, maybe he can right now, but...

21:17.794 --> 21:20.182
Look, it's not gonna be long
before I'm running the company

21:20.188 --> 21:22.755
and no one can stop us
from being together.

21:32.300 --> 21:34.233
- _
- [SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

21:37.505 --> 21:39.805
SHAW: Should <i> I</i> go talk to him?

21:40.007 --> 21:41.876
I think he needs someone right now.

21:41.882 --> 21:44.253
My man's hurting. Him and
Yates went back a long way.

21:44.259 --> 21:45.873
Yes, yes, I know, Shaw.

21:45.879 --> 21:47.946
I'm the one who's in a
relationship with him.

21:48.015 --> 21:50.048
I'm giving him some space.

21:50.117 --> 21:52.618
I'm just saying, if you want
to stay in that relationship,

21:52.687 --> 21:54.711
communication is key.

21:54.717 --> 21:56.990
And I'm just saying: silence.

21:56.996 --> 21:58.928
So Ghazal's body was found inside.

21:58.934 --> 22:00.772
It was meant to look like a suicide.

22:00.778 --> 22:03.791
And given his connections
in the Egyptian intelligence,

22:03.797 --> 22:06.765
I wouldn't expect much
cooperation from there, either.

22:06.771 --> 22:07.876
[SIGHS]

22:07.882 --> 22:09.118
Naturally.

22:09.124 --> 22:11.269
But I found this cell phone.

22:11.338 --> 22:14.106
- Belonged to Yates.
- Agent Karlsson.

22:15.025 --> 22:16.674
Taking evidence from a crime scene?

22:16.680 --> 22:18.135
I can't be a part of this.

22:18.141 --> 22:19.340
What...?

22:19.346 --> 22:21.412
I'm kidding, I can
totally be a part of this.

22:21.418 --> 22:23.042
- [CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
- So you're gonna have Interpol

22:23.048 --> 22:25.283
track where he's been,
retrace his steps?

22:25.415 --> 22:26.980
Yeah. Exactly.

22:26.986 --> 22:28.919
- [CLEARS THROAT]
- Well, since we're all admitting

22:28.925 --> 22:31.526
to stealing evidence
from the crime scene,

22:31.658 --> 22:33.991
I grabbed this from the
bag he was carrying.

22:34.685 --> 22:36.018
Thought it might be useful.

22:36.529 --> 22:37.703
The hard drive

22:37.709 --> 22:39.636
from Ghazal's office.

22:39.761 --> 22:41.328
Not bad.

22:41.334 --> 22:43.485
- Just doing my part.
- Okay.

22:43.491 --> 22:45.722
I am going to finish up
here and have Interpol

22:45.728 --> 22:47.772
trace the last location
Yates used his phone.

22:47.840 --> 22:49.507
Thanks, Gwen.

22:50.002 --> 22:53.737
<i>Cell records show he was here
before he went to Ghazal's.</i>

22:53.743 --> 22:57.148
This must be Yates's safe house.

23:03.622 --> 23:05.555
- Nice work, tiger.
- And voilà.

23:05.561 --> 23:08.295
Not much of a safe house.

23:08.427 --> 23:11.728
Unless he was trying to save the '70s.

23:11.861 --> 23:14.094
Gwen's Intel says he's
been back and forth

23:14.100 --> 23:16.400
to this place twice since he's arrived.

23:16.468 --> 23:18.735
Thought your guy was
following him the whole time.

23:19.133 --> 23:23.034
Like I said, I told him to
be careful <i>not </i> to get caught.

23:23.040 --> 23:25.954
[LAUGHS] And being
careful not to get caught

23:25.960 --> 23:29.028
means he lost track of
Yates multiple times?

23:29.220 --> 23:31.586
Why is everybody coming for me?

23:31.592 --> 23:33.621
LEXI: And we still
don't know if Yates was

23:33.627 --> 23:35.415
working for Reece or the Brotherhood.

23:35.421 --> 23:37.421
SHAW: Hey, we'll find something.

23:38.215 --> 23:39.856
Lex?

23:47.966 --> 23:49.665
Those paintings my dad stole

23:49.671 --> 23:51.673
in the Fensgate Museum heist...

23:51.679 --> 23:53.312
One of them was never recovered.

23:53.318 --> 23:55.851
- You remember which?
- Oh, my God.

23:56.083 --> 23:58.320
<i>The Death of Cleopatra.</i>

23:58.577 --> 24:01.378
Yates didn't work for Reece back then.

24:02.681 --> 24:05.581
This is Reece's apartment.

24:08.189 --> 24:11.790
He's the one behind the heist
that sent my father to prison.

24:19.664 --> 24:22.359
_

24:22.404 --> 24:25.304
[CLOCK CHIMING]

24:25.318 --> 24:26.790
Mr. Reece?

24:27.380 --> 24:29.897
Midge, you can call me Jay. My dad is...

24:30.536 --> 24:32.803
[CLEARS THROAT]

24:32.809 --> 24:35.043
I guess I am Mr. Reece now.

24:35.495 --> 24:38.129
Uh, okay. Is that more
stuff for me to sign?

24:40.978 --> 24:42.548
And, um...

24:43.164 --> 24:45.548
I thought you should also have these.

24:45.554 --> 24:47.121
What are they?

24:47.127 --> 24:48.659
From Egypt,

24:48.695 --> 24:49.927
over the past year.

24:49.996 --> 24:51.361
Why did I never get these?

24:51.430 --> 24:53.064
Your father didn't want you throwing

24:53.070 --> 24:55.537
your whole future away because of her,

24:55.543 --> 24:57.577
but I couldn't bear throwing them out.

24:57.583 --> 24:59.323
It's your company now.

24:59.362 --> 25:01.250
You can decide what to do with them.

25:01.506 --> 25:03.328
The most recent is on top.

25:03.935 --> 25:06.476
If you need me, I'm right outside.

25:32.349 --> 25:33.632
Midge?

25:33.794 --> 25:35.127
Yes, Mr. Reece?

25:38.237 --> 25:40.905
I need you to write a check,
and not from my account

25:40.911 --> 25:42.892
and not from the corporation.
Do you understand?

25:42.898 --> 25:46.349
Yes, sir. I'll contact Mr. Roberge.

25:46.355 --> 25:47.817
He handled many things

25:47.823 --> 25:50.458
for your father, discreetly.

26:00.174 --> 26:01.826
_

26:01.832 --> 26:03.624
DANNY: Now, Reece had my father

26:03.630 --> 26:05.306
steal those other paintings

26:06.257 --> 26:08.771
to cover up the theft of this one.

26:09.367 --> 26:10.869
You were right.

26:10.875 --> 26:12.872
If Reece is behind the heist,

26:12.878 --> 26:15.149
he could be behind Farouk, too.

26:15.712 --> 26:19.228
I keep replaying my
whole life in my head.

26:20.562 --> 26:22.352
I mean, Reece is behind the scholarships

26:22.358 --> 26:24.292
I got to college and law school.

26:25.919 --> 26:27.585
His contacts got me into the FBI

26:27.591 --> 26:30.659
despite having a felon as a father.

26:34.598 --> 26:38.220
My whole life, everything that I am,

26:38.957 --> 26:40.407
is a lie.

26:41.134 --> 26:43.705
A payoff for my father's silence.

26:43.953 --> 26:45.164
Daniel...

26:46.241 --> 26:47.814
You're a good man.

26:48.603 --> 26:52.046
Despite your father, despite Reece,

26:53.213 --> 26:55.049
that's who you are.

27:01.157 --> 27:03.257
You mind if I just have a minute?

27:03.327 --> 27:04.492
Yeah, of course.

27:05.796 --> 27:07.729
- Of course.
- [PHONE BUZZING]

27:10.600 --> 27:13.167
- LEXI: Hello.
- [SIGHS]

27:13.236 --> 27:14.936
It's Simon Hardwick.

27:18.007 --> 27:20.542
Yeah, yeah, okay, hold on.

27:22.277 --> 27:24.119
Simon found something on the bug

27:24.125 --> 27:25.851
he had in the Serapis crypt.

27:28.877 --> 27:30.409
Go ahead, Simon.

27:30.415 --> 27:32.782
HARDWICK: <i>I think I know where
Antony and Cleopatra are.</i>

27:32.788 --> 27:34.484
<i>Alessandro LaLande's family has</i>

27:34.490 --> 27:36.294
<i>been in banking for generations</i>

27:36.359 --> 27:39.626
and also, apparently, the Brotherhood.

27:39.757 --> 27:42.124
<i>From what I can gather,
Antony and Cleopatra</i>

27:42.130 --> 27:43.764
<i>are being held in a vault in</i>

27:43.770 --> 27:45.404
<i>the Banque Saint Laurent in Paris.</i>

27:45.410 --> 27:46.545
[SIGHS]

27:46.866 --> 27:48.297
Good work.

27:48.303 --> 27:50.471
<i>Yeah, well, better move quick.</i>

27:50.477 --> 27:51.868
You've got less than 24 hours.

27:51.874 --> 27:53.707
I think they're being
transported tomorrow.

27:53.713 --> 27:54.844
Where?

27:54.976 --> 27:56.308
<i>That part I can't make out</i>

27:56.314 --> 27:57.568
<i>because of some interference...</i>

27:57.638 --> 28:00.912
You know, I'm gonna send you
the file, and maybe you can.

28:01.279 --> 28:03.551
LEXI: <i>Okay, yeah. We'll call you back.</i>

28:03.557 --> 28:05.658
- Right. Uh...
- [CLICK, BEEP]

28:05.820 --> 28:07.449
Uh...

28:07.938 --> 28:09.638
So you were right.

28:09.957 --> 28:12.308
The Brotherhood did have
Antony and Cleopatra.

28:12.314 --> 28:15.159
And you were right that I had
a blind spot about Reece.

28:15.290 --> 28:17.403
SHAW: You know, it's a
sign of a good relationship

28:17.409 --> 28:19.798
that you both can
accept the middle ground

28:19.804 --> 28:22.338
rather than trying to win the argument.

28:24.037 --> 28:25.970
[PHONE BUZZING]

28:28.308 --> 28:29.641
[CRACKLING OVER RECORDING]

28:29.647 --> 28:31.168
MAN [OVER RECORDING]: <i>Low profile.</i>

28:31.174 --> 28:32.906
<i>We don't want to draw attention.</i>

28:32.912 --> 28:34.809
<i>After the bank closes tomorrow night,</i>

28:34.815 --> 28:36.147
<i>we'll transfer them by truck.</i>

28:36.153 --> 28:37.808
There's some kind of interference.

28:37.814 --> 28:40.047
You know, I was on an investigation once

28:40.053 --> 28:42.871
where we had a recording
device in an office.

28:43.168 --> 28:45.552
We heard the same kind of interference.

28:45.558 --> 28:47.455
When we tried to play
it back, it turned out

28:47.461 --> 28:49.885
another agency was also bugging it.

28:49.891 --> 28:51.391
Two bugs in the same room

28:51.397 --> 28:53.276
transmitting on a similar frequency.

28:53.282 --> 28:55.966
- Exactly.
- So who's the other bug from?

28:57.519 --> 28:59.086
BOTH: Farouk.

28:59.939 --> 29:01.705
If his crew knows

29:01.711 --> 29:03.732
where the Brotherhood is
taking Antony and Cleopatra,

29:03.738 --> 29:06.105
they'll, they'll hit them on the road.

29:06.111 --> 29:07.598
Just like they did the convoy

29:07.604 --> 29:09.192
of Egyptian relics in Geneva.

29:09.882 --> 29:11.816
We got to beat them to it.

29:12.919 --> 29:15.625
We need to rob that bank.

29:18.430 --> 29:20.391
_

29:26.578 --> 29:28.298
SHAW [COCKNEY ACCENT]: Hands up, mate!

29:28.304 --> 29:30.429
Don't you move. Don't be a hero today.

29:30.435 --> 29:32.849
LEXI [COCKNEY ACCENT]: Everybody
out from behind the counter!

29:32.855 --> 29:34.767
- [PEOPLE SCREAMING]
- Get on the ground!

29:35.981 --> 29:38.475
SHAW: We're not here to
hurt anybody in the bank.

29:38.543 --> 29:40.706
All we want is what's in the vault.

29:40.712 --> 29:42.775
You heard him. We haven't got all day.

29:42.781 --> 29:44.435
Keys to the vault.

29:46.484 --> 29:47.916
[CRIES]

29:50.588 --> 29:52.280
You also need the combination to get

29:52.286 --> 29:54.260
you into the vault, and I don't have it.

29:54.804 --> 29:56.156
If you're looking for something

29:56.162 --> 29:57.989
untraceable, I can give you all the cash

29:57.995 --> 29:59.428
and the gold that you can carry.

29:59.434 --> 30:00.847
I just don't want any trouble.

30:00.853 --> 30:02.096
Well, that's too bad, isn't it?

30:02.102 --> 30:04.671
- 'Cause the vault is what we want.
- DANNY: Oi!

30:04.735 --> 30:07.268
[AUSTRALIAN ACCENT]: You don't
know who you're messing with.

30:07.274 --> 30:10.309
This ain't worth dying over... mate.

30:16.067 --> 30:17.927
Give me the combination.

30:17.933 --> 30:19.137
I can't.

30:19.917 --> 30:21.850
You'll need to shoot me.

30:21.856 --> 30:22.954
[PEOPLE WHIMPERING]

30:22.960 --> 30:24.515
LEXI: Okay, we're gonna
do this the hard way.

30:24.521 --> 30:25.887
Cuff him to the table.

30:25.893 --> 30:27.424
Response time's about eight minutes.

30:27.430 --> 30:29.301
- Starting the clock.
- Move!

30:29.307 --> 30:30.988
- Let's go.
- Get down.

30:30.994 --> 30:32.638
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

30:38.068 --> 30:39.900
[REGULAR ACCENT]:
I thought we all agreed,

30:39.906 --> 30:41.838
cockney bank robber accents.

30:41.844 --> 30:44.739
Yeah, that was pure Statham.

30:44.745 --> 30:47.212
- I don't even know what that means.
- Just...

30:47.218 --> 30:48.425
Focus.

30:49.145 --> 30:50.745
[EXHALES]: Okay.

30:50.813 --> 30:53.192
Wasn't sure what kind of
vault we'd be up against,

30:53.198 --> 30:54.658
so I brought options.

30:56.518 --> 30:58.284
[SIRENS WAILING]

30:58.353 --> 30:59.553
[TIRES SCREECH]

31:06.294 --> 31:08.828
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:13.927 --> 31:16.194
SHAW: <i>Hey, guys, we got cops outside.</i>

31:16.200 --> 31:17.667
Damn it, that was fast.

31:17.673 --> 31:20.290
Okay, you keep at it. I'll go up.

31:31.285 --> 31:32.885
What's going on?

31:32.954 --> 31:34.887
Well, they must have heard the gunshot.

31:34.893 --> 31:37.426
Nobody in here had
time to push a button.

31:37.432 --> 31:39.252
Did you?!

31:39.660 --> 31:42.561
Oh, oh, no, no, no, no,
no, no need for that.

31:42.567 --> 31:44.912
We're all good here.
You're going to be fine.

31:44.918 --> 31:46.385
[PHONE RINGING]

31:51.572 --> 31:54.006
Make no attempt to enter the bank,

31:54.075 --> 31:56.274
or I will murder everyone in here.

31:56.280 --> 31:57.401
[CRIES]

31:57.407 --> 31:59.105
[SHUSHES] No, no, no, no,

31:59.111 --> 32:01.441
we're not really going to kill anybody.

32:01.447 --> 32:03.180
We have demands.

32:03.186 --> 32:04.252
Are you ready?

32:04.446 --> 32:06.947
I want a 747 waiting at De Gaulle,

32:06.953 --> 32:09.386
fully fueled with a crew on standby,

32:09.392 --> 32:11.939
as well as a helicopter
to take us there.

32:12.760 --> 32:14.227
And a monster truck.

32:15.397 --> 32:17.711
That's a truck with really big wheels.

32:17.717 --> 32:20.131
You have one hour.

32:24.596 --> 32:26.704
- A monster truck?
- A monster truck.

32:28.674 --> 32:30.174
[DRILL WHIRRING]

32:30.243 --> 32:31.509
All right.

32:31.577 --> 32:33.645
[PANTING]

32:34.088 --> 32:35.787
Yeah.

32:37.499 --> 32:39.198
[GRUNTING]

33:00.572 --> 33:02.839
[CHUCKLES]

33:04.005 --> 33:05.304
SHAW: Um, guys?

33:05.310 --> 33:08.011
I don't think they bothered
with that monster truck.

33:09.281 --> 33:10.914
Holy crap.

33:10.983 --> 33:12.915
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

33:14.252 --> 33:17.320
[OFFICER SPEAKING FRENCH]

33:19.975 --> 33:23.045
_

33:23.051 --> 33:24.794
[SPEAKS FRENCH]

33:25.142 --> 33:26.326
Huh?

33:26.332 --> 33:28.066
They're downstairs.

33:28.633 --> 33:30.567
[FOOTFALLS APPROACHING]

33:30.635 --> 33:32.569
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:00.803 --> 34:05.166
_

34:05.172 --> 34:08.112
_

34:08.118 --> 34:10.091
_

34:10.097 --> 34:12.982
_

34:32.054 --> 34:34.987
Well, how about that?

34:36.850 --> 34:38.783
So, the robbers

34:39.192 --> 34:42.012
just accidentally discovered
Antony and Cleopatra

34:42.018 --> 34:44.592
while they were trying
to break into the vault?

34:44.661 --> 34:46.141
Yeah, it appears so.

34:46.148 --> 34:47.612
They escaped in the chaos.

34:48.563 --> 34:51.386
The bank manager...
he disappeared as well.

34:51.572 --> 34:53.136
The police cruiser taking him

34:53.141 --> 34:54.812
to the station never arrived,

34:54.818 --> 34:58.286
so no one knows or can
explain how they got here.

34:58.292 --> 34:59.835
- [CHUCKLES]
- LEXI: Reece,

34:59.841 --> 35:01.741
this is Simon Hardwick.

35:01.747 --> 35:03.264
He's the one who spotted the robbers

35:03.270 --> 35:04.529
and alerted the authorities.

35:04.535 --> 35:06.011
Without him, Antony and Cleopatra

35:06.017 --> 35:07.816
- might have never been recovered.
- Oh...

35:07.822 --> 35:10.341
HARDWICK: Mr. Reece, it means
the world to finally meet you.

35:10.347 --> 35:12.855
Funny enough, I'm also in
the antique-dealing business.

35:12.861 --> 35:14.293
Thank you so much, Mr. Warwick.

35:14.299 --> 35:16.399
I insist that you accompany us

35:16.405 --> 35:18.004
for the public unveiling.

35:18.010 --> 35:19.823
I'll have my secretary contact you.

35:19.829 --> 35:21.534
She'll make all the arrangements.

35:21.805 --> 35:23.266
Uh, well, thank you.

35:23.272 --> 35:25.245
- Uh, that's a great honor.
- Danny,

35:25.948 --> 35:27.506
can you believe this?

35:27.575 --> 35:29.795
Lot of things I can't believe today.

35:29.962 --> 35:31.595
Can you and I talk?

35:31.623 --> 35:33.732
Yeah. Excuse me.

35:38.980 --> 35:40.330
[DANNY SIGHS]

35:40.336 --> 35:42.675
Um... [CHUCKLES] Kid,
you're making me nervous.

35:42.681 --> 35:44.557
- What's up, somebody die?
- Yeah.

35:44.714 --> 35:45.940
Rick Yates.

35:45.946 --> 35:47.229
- What?
- In Egypt.

35:47.612 --> 35:50.396
After shooting at me and Lexi.

35:50.402 --> 35:51.876
Wait, I don't understand.

35:51.882 --> 35:54.567
He stole evidence related
to the Farouk investigation.

35:54.573 --> 35:57.807
I have no idea about any of that.

35:57.813 --> 36:00.465
You can't think I was somehow
in league with Farouk.

36:00.471 --> 36:02.090
Yates was a traitor.

36:02.096 --> 36:03.617
You know, I-I honestly... I don't know

36:03.623 --> 36:05.156
what to think anymore.

36:05.535 --> 36:08.870
Danny, Farouk blew up
one of my pipelines.

36:08.876 --> 36:10.380
My company had an office in

36:10.386 --> 36:12.126
the tower that Farouk hit in Malaysia.

36:12.132 --> 36:15.055
The man has been at war
with my company for years.

36:15.061 --> 36:17.194
Yates was working out of
your apartment in Egypt.

36:17.200 --> 36:19.557
- My apartment...
- Stop it, Jay.

36:20.114 --> 36:23.261
<i>The Death of Cleopatra</i>
painting, I found it.

36:24.498 --> 36:26.971
I know you're behind the
Fensgate Museum heist.

36:26.977 --> 36:29.677
Only thing I don't know is
what else you're guilty of.

36:31.638 --> 36:33.938
[CHUCKLES]

36:34.007 --> 36:36.241
Do you know that for decades

36:36.309 --> 36:38.300
I have dreaded...

36:38.932 --> 36:40.828
Probably on some level

36:40.834 --> 36:42.480
<i>hoped</i> for this moment?

36:44.769 --> 36:47.069
The Fensgate Museum heist...

36:48.813 --> 36:51.280
... was the biggest mistake I ever made.

36:51.959 --> 36:53.754
I was told

36:53.872 --> 36:56.840
that it would be easy.

36:56.942 --> 36:59.217
No one would get hurt.

36:59.223 --> 37:01.323
I just wanted one painting.

37:02.081 --> 37:04.581
Why was it so important to you?

37:06.039 --> 37:07.638
Belonged to my father.

37:09.542 --> 37:11.515
You know, he rescued that painting

37:11.843 --> 37:13.678
during the Second World War.

37:14.085 --> 37:15.895
Then, decades later,

37:15.901 --> 37:17.349
somebody shows up

37:17.355 --> 37:19.988
out of nowhere and says it's theirs.

37:21.141 --> 37:23.336
And I don't even fight it.
I just give it to them.

37:24.051 --> 37:27.853
Then they turn around
and sell it to the Fensgate.

37:27.968 --> 37:30.818
That painting would have been destroyed

37:30.960 --> 37:32.747
if it hadn't been for my father.

37:32.753 --> 37:35.787
In my heart, it was his.

37:37.326 --> 37:38.783
Mine.

37:39.440 --> 37:40.739
And so I took it.

37:40.745 --> 37:42.616
You had my dad take it.

37:42.622 --> 37:44.222
No, I have never forgiven myself

37:44.228 --> 37:46.261
for what happened to your father.

37:47.279 --> 37:48.378
To you.

37:48.563 --> 37:50.556
That's why I've done
everything I could for you.

37:50.562 --> 37:52.896
Don't-don't lie to me, Jay.

37:53.252 --> 37:55.452
You did it to buy my father's silence.

37:55.521 --> 37:57.187
At the beginning, yes, that's true.

37:57.256 --> 37:59.300
But I am not lying to you

37:59.655 --> 38:03.392
when I say that I have
loved you like a son.

38:08.002 --> 38:11.187
You know I have two
ex-wives, three daughters.

38:12.722 --> 38:15.223
None of them speak to me.

38:16.779 --> 38:18.478
Danny, you're the only thing in my life

38:18.484 --> 38:20.284
that I am truly proud of.

38:22.729 --> 38:24.429
Look, we...

38:24.435 --> 38:27.403
Egypt has suffered a tragedy.

38:27.785 --> 38:30.556
We can bring healing to this country.

38:30.562 --> 38:33.029
We can bring the world together.

38:33.035 --> 38:36.118
And that's what this has been all about.

38:37.962 --> 38:40.895
Look, once this is all over...

38:42.987 --> 38:44.375
... I will confess...

38:45.417 --> 38:48.091
My part of what happened
at the Fensgate.

38:49.303 --> 38:51.569
I will return the painting.

38:53.689 --> 38:55.910
I would only ask that you be my lawyer.

39:00.784 --> 39:02.487
I don't think I can do that.

39:03.516 --> 39:05.616
But I will walk with you into the FBI

39:05.622 --> 39:07.554
and make sure it all gets done.

39:09.429 --> 39:11.814
I'll give you a couple days
to make your arrangements.

39:24.740 --> 39:26.674
<i>Un pacco per Charles Donnelly.</i>

39:27.055 --> 39:29.039
<i>Firmo io. Grazie.</i>

39:29.045 --> 39:30.399
<i>Prego.</i>

39:30.779 --> 39:32.453
<i>- Ciao.
- Ciao.</i>

39:52.434 --> 39:53.732
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

39:55.084 --> 39:57.210
Come in, come in.

39:57.216 --> 39:59.516
Look at these pictures.

39:59.716 --> 40:01.866
We're building a replica of the tomb,

40:01.872 --> 40:04.944
and a brand-new wing
in my museum in Egypt.

40:04.950 --> 40:06.442
Making it a rush job,
but the anniversary

40:06.448 --> 40:08.314
of Cleopatra's death is coming.

40:08.320 --> 40:10.253
It's costing me a fortune,
but what better way

40:10.259 --> 40:12.350
to unveil her to the world?

40:13.221 --> 40:15.053
It's amazing, Jay.

40:16.991 --> 40:18.323
You need to cancel it.

40:19.729 --> 40:21.189
What? Absolutely not.

40:21.195 --> 40:22.961
I've got people working around the clock

40:22.967 --> 40:24.392
ever since we discovered Antony.

40:24.398 --> 40:26.214
Farouk is going to attack it.

40:26.220 --> 40:29.075
- Farouk is dead.
- Then his men will attack it.

40:29.973 --> 40:32.300
A check was found made to a Zara Farouk.

40:32.306 --> 40:34.997
We didn't know who she was
until we looked into it.

40:36.377 --> 40:38.263
This is a...

40:39.092 --> 40:41.679
Record from a mosque in Egypt.

40:41.748 --> 40:43.915
It is a certificate from a Sebou,

40:43.984 --> 40:46.118
which is an Egyptian
custom that celebrates

40:46.124 --> 40:48.268
the seventh day of a baby's birth.

40:48.274 --> 40:50.505
On it, it lists Karim Farouk's

40:50.511 --> 40:52.294
mother as Zara Farouk,

40:52.635 --> 40:54.837
and also his father.

40:55.257 --> 40:57.558
- [POURING DRINK]
- Jay, did you know

40:57.564 --> 40:59.597
that you were Karim Farouk's father?

41:00.486 --> 41:02.534
I've known for years.

41:04.464 --> 41:06.664
I was young, I met a girl...

41:06.670 --> 41:08.569
Oh, I know how babies are made, Jay.

41:08.575 --> 41:11.108
I don't care that you fathered someone

41:11.114 --> 41:12.280
who became a terrorist.

41:12.286 --> 41:13.841
I mean, you had no idea.

41:13.847 --> 41:15.647
You couldn't help what he would become.

41:15.715 --> 41:18.382
That's not how the
world would see it, Ana.

41:18.388 --> 41:19.719
Everything I've ever worked for

41:19.725 --> 41:21.344
would be destroyed forever.

41:21.350 --> 41:23.917
Farouk weaponized a
toxin that killed Zara.

41:23.923 --> 41:26.857
This is obviously very personal to him.

41:26.926 --> 41:28.640
And the people who followed him,

41:28.646 --> 41:30.466
they're gonna use this unveiling

41:30.472 --> 41:32.605
to kill you and so many more people.

41:32.611 --> 41:35.088
I am tired of living,
looking over my shoulder.

41:36.432 --> 41:39.266
Perhaps I can get rid of all of them

41:39.272 --> 41:40.904
- once and for all.
- You know what?

41:40.973 --> 41:43.244
I thought that I could come here today

41:43.250 --> 41:45.405
to reason with you, but...

41:45.411 --> 41:48.245
If I can't do that, then...

41:48.251 --> 41:49.517
[GASPING]

41:49.523 --> 41:52.027
... I'm gonna have to go to
the authorities. [GASPING]

41:52.033 --> 41:54.004
I know, I know, I know,
I know, come here.

41:54.010 --> 41:55.715
Come and sit down. Sit down.

41:55.721 --> 41:58.221
- Sit down.
- [GASPING]

42:01.259 --> 42:04.062
Ana, why did you always
have to be so smart?

42:04.693 --> 42:06.325
I was afraid it would come to this.

42:06.331 --> 42:07.831
But you have...

42:08.897 --> 42:11.898
Helped me sever the one tie I have

42:11.904 --> 42:14.142
to that maniac.

42:16.762 --> 42:19.663
Maybe you're the last
person who has to die

42:19.764 --> 42:22.545
in the name of Karim Farouk.

